<item>
            <title>[PIG-3253] Misleading comment w.r.t getSplitIndex() method in PigSplit.java</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3253</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While reviewing the patch for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3141&quot; title=&quot;Giving CSVExcelStorage an option to handle header rows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3141&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3141&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I noticed that the following comment is out-of-date:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;PigSplit.java&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;package&lt;/span&gt; level access because we don&apos;t want LoadFunc implementations
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// to get &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; information - &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; is to be used only from
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// MergeJoinIndexer
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; getSplitIndex() {
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; splitIndex;
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Looking at the commit history, the public qualifier was added by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-1309&quot; title=&quot;Sort Merge Cogroup&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-1309&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-1309&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but the comment wasn&apos;t updated accordingly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Provided that more and more LoadFunc implementations use this method (e.g. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3141&quot; title=&quot;Giving CSVExcelStorage an option to handle header rows&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3141&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3141&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;), we should remove this misleading comment to avoid any confusion.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
